23:13.892 --> 23:15.560
They're not gonna be easy to get back.

23:15.644 --> 23:18.355
Well, Ms. Austero isn't quite
a missing person yet.

23:18.563 --> 23:21.566
We are particularly interested
in talking to Byron,

23:21.650 --> 23:23.443
who she apparently
had a relationship with.

23:23.527 --> 23:26.822
It's Buster. Uh, and that's why I know
that they're up to something,

23:26.905 --> 23:29.991
'cause the last time
that I saw Buster was, um...

23:30.075 --> 23:31.493
- Oh, God!
- [yells]

23:31.576 --> 23:33.954
[Ron] <i>And, resentful of his family,</i>

23:34.037 --> 23:36.498
<i>Michael came up with a plan
to make them come back.</i>

23:36.581 --> 23:38.166
Tell me how
this missing person thing works.

23:38.250 --> 23:40.669
- You want to report him missing?
- I might.

23:40.752 --> 23:44.464
You'd call it in,
but not until he's been gone for 72 hours.

23:44.548 --> 23:46.800
Hmm. I think it's worth the wait.

23:46.883 --> 23:48.510
Yeah, yeah. Yeah, okay.

23:48.593 --> 23:51.221
That's what we'll do.
Find Buster, you're gonna find Lucille.

23:51.304 --> 23:52.347
Which one?

23:52.431 --> 23:53.598
I don't think he cares.

23:55.350 --> 23:56.393
See you later.

23:58.395 --> 23:59.771
Thank you for your service.

24:02.232 --> 24:03.191
Love you.

24:03.275 --> 24:04.776
[elevator bell dings]

24:09.448 --> 24:13.577
[Ron] <i>Lindsay arrives at the border</i>
<i>she had just called for a wall to protect.</i>

24:13.660 --> 24:15.287
[Lindsay] Oh, they have one.

24:17.080 --> 24:18.582
[laughs nervously]

24:18.665 --> 24:20.542
[speaking Spanish]

24:20.625 --> 24:21.877
He wants your passport.

24:21.960 --> 24:23.879
Oh, I didn't bring a... [scoffs]
I'm American.

24:23.962 --> 24:25.630
How do you say "I'm American"
in Mexican?

24:25.714 --> 24:26.965
<i>Soy americano.</i>

24:27.048 --> 24:30.135
Hmm. That does sound good.
Ask him for two.

24:31.178 --> 24:32.471
[Ron] <i>Lindsay is proud</i>

24:32.554 --> 24:34.556
<i>that she thought to include her driver.</i>

24:36.349 --> 24:38.560
<i>And Lucille and her therapist arrive</i>

24:38.643 --> 24:40.854
<i>- at their beachside </i> casita.
- [Lucille] Look at them.

24:40.937 --> 24:43.690
Dancing on the beach
like they own the place.

24:44.649 --> 24:47.110
Good. We'll use that.

24:47.194 --> 24:49.196
I want to laser in on that anger.

24:49.279 --> 24:50.697
Look out at the ocean.

24:51.114 --> 24:53.783
Tell me, what does it make you think?

24:54.367 --> 24:57.537
Like, "Everyone's having fun but me,

24:57.621 --> 25:00.081
running and laughing and...

25:00.165 --> 25:02.042
I feel like men run away from me.

25:02.125 --> 25:04.920
- I'm stuck here doing therapy."
- I've been deserted.

25:05.003 --> 25:07.881
Is that my fault?
Is it because of my anger?

25:08.965 --> 25:11.843
When I see a squirrelly,
little fruitcake like that one

25:11.927 --> 25:14.012
skipping into the ocean, I think,

25:14.095 --> 25:17.891
- "Why do I hate him so much?"
- [man laughing outside]

25:17.974 --> 25:20.602
That little bald one there
with the fringed cut-offs who...

25:20.685 --> 25:22.729
- [Tobias] Yay!
- [Lucille] Oh, [bleeps].

25:22.812 --> 25:23.939
It's you.

25:24.898 --> 25:26.483
[Tobias continues laughing]

